Application → Service → Labels → DestinationRule → VirtualService → Sidecar Injection → Envoy Configuration → Traffic Verification
Stage 1: Are the pods running?
kubectl get pods

Expected:

reviews-v1   2/2 Running
reviews-v2   2/2 Running
reviews-v3   2/2 Running
Problem symptoms
CrashLoopBackOff
Pending
ImagePullBackOff
Fix

Check:

kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
kubectl logs <pod-name>
Stage 2: Does the Service see all pods?
kubectl describe svc reviews

Expected:

Endpoints:
100.96.1.66:9080
100.96.3.137:9080
100.96.2.164:9080
Problem

No endpoints:

Endpoints: <none>
Root cause

Service selector doesn't match pod labels.

Stage 3: Do pod labels match subsets?

Check:

kubectl get pods --show-labels

Expected:

reviews-v1 version=v1
reviews-v2 version=v2
reviews-v3 version=v3

Compare with:

subsets:
- name: v1
  labels:
    version: v1
Common issue

Pod label:

version: V1

DestinationRule:

version: v1

(case-sensitive mismatch)

Stage 4: DestinationRule created?

Check:

kubectl get destinationrule
kubectl describe destinationrule reviews
Error
no matches for kind "DestinationRule"
Root cause

Istio CRDs not installed.

Stage 5: VirtualService correct?

Check:

kubectl describe virtualservice reviews

Example:

http:
- route:
  - destination:
      host: reviews
      subset: v2
    weight: 10
  - destination:
      host: reviews
      subset: v3
    weight: 90
Problems

Weights don't add up to 100.

Wrong subset name:

subset: version2

but DestinationRule contains:

name: v2
Stage 6: Is sidecar injected?

This was your issue.

You checked:

kubectl get pods

Initially:

1/1 Running

That means:

❌ No Envoy sidecar

Hence:

❌ VirtualService ignored

❌ Canary not working

Enable:

kubectl label namespace default istio-injection=enabled

Restart:

kubectl delete pods --all

Then:

2/2 Running

Meaning:

✅ Envoy sidecar present

Stage 7: Is Envoy receiving configuration?

Best command:

istioctl proxy-config clusters <productpage-pod>

Expected:

reviews|9080|v1
reviews|9080|v2
reviews|9080|v3
Problem

Only:

reviews|9080

means subsets weren't loaded.

