for i in {1..100}
do
curl http://<LB-IP>/productpage
done
Stage 9: Watch logs

Terminal 1:

kubectl logs -f deploy/reviews-v2 -c reviews

Terminal 2:

kubectl logs -f deploy/reviews-v3 -c reviews

If:

v2 = 10%
v3 = 90%

then:

few requests → v2
many requests → v3
Real interview troubleshooting flow

When someone says:

"Canary deployment is not working"

I investigate in this order:

1. Pod health
2. Service endpoints
3. Pod labels
4. DestinationRule
5. VirtualService
6. Sidecar injection
7. Envoy config
8. Application logs
9. Traffic generation
